                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/20026</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-12-06T17:00:00-07:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 6, 1916, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Messages received here stating that Parral is again in hands of Carranza troops
                    and that Americans are safe and no property destroyed. There is a noticeable
                    improvement in conditions in Juarez, fear of change of government now dispelled.
                    The contention and dissension known to exist between Generals Obregon and
                    Treviño which has been the cause of inactivity and given encouragement to the
                    bandits is thought to be over and that better results will come from Government
                    forces.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwards</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
